cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.HC, cs.AI 

This paper primarily focuses on the use of a Brain-Computer Interface (BCI) for teleoperation of a humanoid robot in a natural indoor environment. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also heavily relies on deep Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) based image understanding and signal decoding, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the use of BCI involves human subjects and their cognitive processes, which could place the paper in cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). Finally, the paper proposes a novel approach for using variable BCI stimuli, which could also be relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) research.
